<h2 id="context">Context</h2>

<p>This puzzle was one of the puzzles we wrote to include in our wedding book.</p>

<h2 id="hints">Hints</h2>

<div class="panel-group" id="accordion">
                    <div class="panel panel-default">
                        <div class="panel-heading">
                            <div class="panel-title">
                                <a class="noCrossRef accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne">How do I get started with this?</a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseOne" class="panel-collapse collapse noCrossRef">
                            <div class="panel-body">
                            To start, focus on words that have As and Js in weird patterns. For instance, JACINDA ARDERN has two As in a row and TAJ MAHAL has a lot of As and Js in a small amount of space. Whenever you put a word in the grid, fill in the boxes right in front of and right behind the words so you know that other letters cannot go in them.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
  </div>

